{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Formal consensus APPROVED on all 4 follow-ups",
    "content": "Marty Cagan -- formal consensus: APPROVED.\n\nProduct review confirms all 4 follow-ups are well-scoped quality and accessibility improvements with no MVP scope expansion:\n\n1. **Completed-todo axe scan** -- Covers a core user state. Users mark items done constantly; ensuring that styling passes contrast checks protects the everyday reading experience.\n2. **wcag22aa tag** -- Closes the gap between our Definition of Done (WCAG 2.2 AA) and actual test coverage. Necessary compliance alignment.\n3. **JSON.stringify formatting** -- Developer experience improvement that pays for itself on the first a11y test failure. No user-facing impact, no added complexity.\n4. **Forced-colors border fix** -- Windows High Contrast Mode users need visible button boundaries. This is not an edge case -- it is inclusive design done right.\n\nNo concerns. Ship it."
  }
}
